
Preheat oven to 400 F. Grease 24 muffin cups with butter. 

Whisk 2 eggs and 3/4 c brown sugar in a medium bowl until smooth. Add 1 c 
buttermilk, 1 c mashed banana, 1/4 c oil, and 1 tsp vanilla and whisk until 
blended. In a large bowl, whisk 2 1/2 c flour, 1 1/2 tsp baking powder, 1/2 tsp
baking soda, 1 tsp salt, and 1/2 tsp cinnamon. Make a well in the dry 
ingredients and pour in the wet ingredients. Add 1 c chocolate chips and mix 
with a rubber spatula until just combined.

Spoon batter into greased muffin cups and mix a sprinkle of chopped nuts into
the tops. Bake until tops spring back when touched lightly, about 12-15 
minutes.

Makes about 2 dozen muffins.


Ingredients:
2 eggs
3/4 c brown sugar
1 c buttermilk
1 c mashed banana (2 medium bananas)
1/4 c vegetable oil
1 tsp vanilla extract
2 1/2 c whole wheat flour
1 1/2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp baking soda
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp cinnamon
1 c chocolate chips
2 tbsp chopped walnuts or pecans
Butter for the muffin tins
